messages.text: D!!! Are you there??
PLEASE TELL ME YOU’RE THERE
Girl, this better be good.
I’m in the middle of bingeing the last season of Real Housewives to unwind.
I got this weird cryptic note card in my locker this afternoon.
What, like a party flier for one of James’ parties?
No. It says CLUE ONE with poetry and a page number (39)...
then at the end it says “Come Find Me. Expires by 7pm”
What’s the poetry?
“He stepped down, trying not to look long at her, as if she were the sun,
yet he saw her, like the sun, even without looking.”
I just googled it.
And??
Not poetry. It’s a quote from Anna Karenina by Leo Tolstoy.
What does that mean??
I think it means some creepy dude who likes classic chick lit likes you.
Do you think it’s Steve??
Bitch, please. Steve probably can’t even spell his own name...
let alone read a piece of read literature.
Don’t talk about him like that!
Laney - the only interaction you’ve ever had with the dude...
was when you tagged yourself in one of his fb photos by mistake...
while you were stalking him on your phone
I deleted it before he saw it!
You’ve been pining over this guy for years, and he’s done nothing.
Let it go.
But maybe he’s done nothing because he’s too SHY, so he wants to leave this cryptic note.
I saw him looking at me after gym class the other week.
I looked at you at lunch, doesn’t mean I want to have sex with you.
It wasn’t like that.
Were you wearing your all yellow Spongebob shirt?
Yes...
Case dismissed. Though maybe he IS writing that and complaining about your shirt.
It is like the fucking sun, and if you stare at it too close you go blind.
From bad taste.
Shut up, and there’s only one way to find out. Page 39.
My Mom might have a copy of the book. She reads that shit.
I don’t think the next clue is just going to be in any copy.
It was written on a note card that looks like it comes from the library.
And he said it expires at 7, when it closes I’m guessing.
Well you better get there before someone takes it out.
Yeah, so here’s the problem.
Here we go
I have my Grandpa’s birthday dinner in an hour.
No way it will be over by then.
You heard I was watching Real Housewives, right?
Shit’s about to be tore up and I’m in my footie PJs.
Come on, D. Please. You have a car. It won’t take that long.
I don’t have a car.
I have my Mom’s car and I don’t know if she’ll let me use it right now.
If she knows you’re going to the library, she’ll let you borrow it.
And probably have a heart attack.
Hey! I read!
Cosmo magazine... And...
Fine. But I’m stopping at Uncle Dood’s Donuts before and enjoying myself a Funky Monkey first.
Whatever you need to power you through. Just please go...
I’m not changing out of my pajamas!
Fine... Wait. What if he’s there?
Maybe that’s ideal.
I can screen for you to see if maybe it’s that weird dude who used to make you origami birds are freshman year.
Sweet. Talk soon.
two hours later
D What’s the progress?
Not gonna lie, but I had 4 Funky Monkeys instead of one and feel a little sugar nuts.
I mean what’s the progress AT THE LIBRARY MORON
Calm yourself, I’m in the classics section now.
I’m too nervous to eat! I’ve been thinking what if this is the love of my life??
Most specifically what if it IS Steve...
and I don’t have to memorize his schedule anymore so I can coordinate walking past him in the hallway?!
Because he’s actually just HOLDING MY HAND AS WE WALK DOWN IT TOGETHER!!!
He should’ve filed a restraining order already.
Besides, my Mom says teen love has as much meaning as a bowl of Fruit Loops.
I can see where you get your glowing optimism from.
Well? Have you found it?
YES!
WELL???
Hello?
Daryl???
Well, it WAS here. But some asshole from High School East took it!
WHAT!? WHAT ASSHOLE!?
I think we went to Intermediate school with him. Alan something.
WELL DON’T JUST LET HIM TAKE IT!!!
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO, WRESTLE IT FROM HIM???
YOU ONLY NEED TO LOOK AT PAGE 39!
OK
Wait... WAIT. Oh my god...I just had a thought.
What if THIS is the guy, and he’s trying to protect you from taking the book, because it’s not me?!
DARYL!?
HELLO!?!??
DUDE. WHAT IS GOING ON??
Okay, so what happened was: he’s not the guy.
He had NO idea what I was talking about when I threatened him about it.
When I tried to get it back from him...
we had a bit of a tug of war that ended in him falling back into the elderly librarian...
who then fell into a children’s display...
and who is now on the floor moaning about her hip...
Oh shit.
Also - I just got escorted outside by a security guard.
Shit!!! SO HE HAS THE BOOK.
But, I won the tug of war...and tore out page 39 before I got escorted out.
WHAT!??
The Dood’s donuts give me strength. Your next clue is:
“The universe is full of magic things, patiently waiting for our senses to grow sharper.”
7001 Franklin Ave. 10PM. Ask Irma to play your next clue.
Irma?
It’s the Magic Castle.
And yes, I’ll drive.
But we’re stopping at the Russian bakery so I can get some vatrushka first!
